cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.LG, cs.DM, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with algorithms for querying approximate farthest neighbors in a metric space, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and data structures. This makes cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) the most likely categories. The paper also involves techniques for reducing the weighted problem to the unweighted problem, which is related to approximation algorithms and optimization, and hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) are also likely categories. Finally, the paper mentions an application to network topology, which involves information theory and communication, and hence cs.IT (Information Theory) is a possible category as well.
